name: rb-jekyll-swiss
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "jekyll-swiss" %}
{% set version = "1.0.0" %}

package:
  name: rb-{{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://rubygems.org/downloads/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.gem
  sha256: c299a855dca881fe868f21545c5489be50ddfbc0d54a80e8dbeb5a2ddc4888a3

build:
  noarch: generic
  number: 1
  script:
    - gem install -N -l -V --norc --ignore-dependencies {{ name }}-{{ version }}.gem
    - gem unpack {{ name }}-{{ version }}.gem
  skip: {{ win }}

requirements:
  host:
    - ruby
  run:
    - ruby

test:
  commands:
    - gem list -i {{ name }} -v {{ version }}

about:
  home: https://rubygems.org/gems/{{ name }}
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: {{ name }}-{{ version }}/LICENSE.txt
  summary: A bold typographic theme for Jekyll, inspired by Swiss design.

  doc_url: https://www.rubydoc.info/gems/{{ name }}
  dev_url: https://github.com/benbalter/{{ name }}

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - sodre
